Bollore, Ion Beam, Zodiac Aerospace: European Equity Preview

-- B y   C e c i l e   V a n n u c c i
-- 
2011-03-16T04:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/bollore-ion-beam-zodiac-aerospace-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index dropped 2.3 percent to 266.32.
The Stoxx 50 Index declined 2.2 percent to 2,510.04. The Euro
Stoxx 50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, fell 2.4
percent to 2,784.20.    Bollore (BOL)  SA: The French holding company with stakes
in freight, transport, paper and rubber operations said 2010 net
income rose to 317 million euros from 94 million euros a year
earlier. The stock fell 2.9 percent to 152.35 euros.    Ion Beam Applications (IBAB)  SA: Europe’s largest maker
of proton-therapy equipment forecast 2011 net income will drop
from 6.23 million euros and doesn’t expect its pharmaceuticals
division to break even before 2015 as spending will exceed 100
million euros over five years. Ion Beam fell 4.5 percent to 8.36
euros.    RHJ International (RHJI)  SA: The owner of U.K. wealth
manager  Kleinwort Benson  said RIT Capital Plc reduced its stake
to 2.95 percent of  voting rights  as of March 7 from 3.31 percent
previously. RHJ decreased 3.1 percent to 5.67 euros.    Zodiac Aerospace (ZC)  : Europe’s biggest maker of
aircraft seats said first-half revenue rose to 1.31 billion
euros from 966 million euros a year earlier. The stock fell 2.2
percent to 46.96 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecile Vannucci in New York at 
